2)SX1276
The SX1276/77/78/79 transceivers-- LoRa long range modem that provides ultra-long range spread spectrum communication and high interference immunity with minimum current consumption.
can achieve a sensitivity of over -148dBm
integrated +20dBm power amplifier
detailed documentation and how-to guides
FREQUENCY RANGE : 137Mhz to 1.02GHz
SUPPLY VOLTAGE(min/max) : 1.8/3.7 V
BANDWIDHT: 7.8-500kHz
SPREADING FACTOR : 6-12
EFFECTIVE BITRATE : .018 - 37.5 kbps
SENSITIVITY (estimated): -111 to -148 dBm
( using a low cost bill of materials with a 20ppm XTAL LoRa can improve receiver sensitivity by more than 20dB)
COST: 522.85(+1200/- for delivery)
168dB maximum link budget
+20dBm - 100mW constant RF output vs. V supply
+14 dBm high efficiency PA
Programmable bit rate up to 300kbps
Low RX current of 9.9mA, 200nA register retention
URLs:
Datasheet : https://www.mouser.in/pdfdocs/sx1276_77_78_79.pdf
